comments: Professor Sneed\'s class was a semi tough one. So for the reading, make sure to understand whay you\'re reading and if you don\'t come to class. That discussion you have in class is super important. The tests are 85% on that discussion I guarantee you. Participate, record if you have to. The summaries are IMPORTANT. Do all this and you\'d be fine.

comments: Every stereotype about what a smug person likes and is like applies to him. His lectures are rarely on the actual topic of the class, but instead can often be described as "I\'m better than you, and here\'s why." To top it off, he doesn\'t even grade the tests or homeworks himself. He paid someone else to do it. There should be rules against this.

comments: Acts more like a class clown than a professor. Spent way too much talking about politics and chess. His humor either complimented his lectures or got in the way. He\'s unorganized and prone to going on many tangents. Read the textbook and come to class and you\'ll be fine. His lectures can be frustrating, informative and/or hilariously bewildering.
